title: Chicken Ramen Stir-Fry
summary: The recipe Chicken Ramen Stir-Fry could satisfy your Japanese craving in roughly 45 minutes. This recipe makes 4 servings with 436 calories, 20g of protein, and 23g of fat each. For $1.72 per serving, this recipe covers 24% of your daily requirements of vitamins and minerals. This recipe is liked by 55 foodies and cooks. It works well as a rather cheap main course. If you have reduced sodium soy sauce, vegetable oil, sesame oil, and a few other ingredients on hand, you can make it. All things considered, we decided this recipe deserves a spoonacular score of 79%. This score is pretty good. Try Chicken and Broccoli Stir-Fry, Quick Chicken & Broccoli Stir-Fry, and Quick 15 Minute Stir-Fry Chicken and Veggies for similar recipes.

winePairing.pairingText: Riesling, Sake, and Sauvignon Blanc are my top picks for Ramen Noodles. Saké is an obvious choice when it comes to Japanese food. If you want to stick to grape wine, though, you might opt for sauvignon blanc or riesling. The Bollig-Lehnert Piesporter Goldtroopfchen Riesling Spatlese with a 4.5 out of 5 star rating seems like a good match. It costs about 24 dollars per bottle.

instructions: Bring medium size pan of water to boil. Add Ramen noodles and cook them according to package directions. Drain and stir in 1 Tbsp of vegetable oil. Set aside.                        In a large skillet heat 2 Tbsp vegetable oil over high heat. Add chicken and cook until chicken is cooked through and no longer pink, about 5-7 minutes. Remove from skillet and set aside.                         Add broccoli, coleslaw mix, and garlic and saute for 3-5 minutes. Add ginger and fry for another two minutes.                         Meanwhile in a mixing bowl combine chicken broth, soy sauce, cornstarch, sesame oil, and Truva Brown Sugar Blend and mix until blended.                         Add chicken, Ramen noodles, broth mixture into skillet and cook until heated through.                         Garnish with sesame seeds if desired.

steps.step: Bring medium size pan of water to boil.
Add Ramen noodles and cook them according to package directions.
Drain and stir in 1 Tbsp of vegetable oil. Set aside.
In a large skillet heat 2 Tbsp vegetable oil over high heat.
Add chicken and cook until chicken is cooked through and no longer pink, about 5-7 minutes.
Remove from skillet and set aside.
Add broccoli, coleslaw mix, and garlic and saute for 3-5 minutes.
Add ginger and fry for another two minutes.
Meanwhile in a mixing bowl combine chicken broth, soy sauce, cornstarch, sesame oil, and Truva Brown Sugar Blend and mix until blended.
Add chicken, Ramen noodles, broth mixture into skillet and cook until heated through.
Garnish with sesame seeds if desired.
